### tests/markers_negation.crit — exercise the `not on <m>` / `<m> == 0`
### sugar forms. All four new spellings desugar to the canonical
### `if on no marker <m>` / `if no marker <m>` the engine already
### handles — this fixture just proves the grammar compiles. Semantic
### identity with the canonical form is covered by the existing marker
### fixtures.
###
### Pass criterion: compiles clean. (Rejection test harness: absence of
### a `markers_*` rejection category => clean compile required.)

--- colors ---
ant:   (0, 255, 255)
trail: ramp (3.0, 3.0, 3.0) decay 0/1

--- landmarks ---
zone: trail
  (4, 4)
  (5, 4)
  (6, 4)

--- agents ---
up to 1 ant
ant starts at (5, 4)

--- simulation ---
tick rate: 100ms

--- behavior ---
ant:
  # Self-cell inverses — both mean "this cell has no trail".
  if not on trail:
    pause 1
    done
  if not standing on trail:
    pause 1
    done

  # `== 0` aliases for `no`.
  if on trail == 0:
    pause 1
    done
  if trail == 0:
    pause 1
    done
  if trail == 0 on landmark zone:
    pause 1
    done

  pause 1
  done
